If SIR uses 12 decimals after the comma, 'uint80' is sufficient to store ALL SIR issued over 599 years 2,015,000,000 sir/year * 599 years * 10^12 \u2264 type(uint80).max Maximum TEA Supply The previous choice implies that if wish to store struct LPerIssuanceParams in a single slot (256 bits), cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 can use up to 96 bits for the decimals (Q80.96) It is important that cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 does not underflow (if it is 0 it would wrongly imply that the LPers have not claim to any SIR): cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 = 8/10 * 63.9 SIR/s * 10^12 * timeInterval * 2^96 * (tax / cumulativeTax) / T In the worst case scenario: timeInterval=1s, tax=1, cumulativeTax=type(uint16).max and TEA has 18 decimals. So to avoid underflow: T \u2264 8/10 * 63.9 * 10^12 * 2^96 / (2^16-1) If TEA has 18 decimals Max Supply of TEA = T / 10^18 \u2248 6.18 * 10^19 which is more than a Quintillion TEA, sufficient for almost any ERC-20."}},"kind":"user","methods":{"burn(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256)":{"notice":"Function for burning APE or TEA, the protocol's synthetic tokens.When burning APE, the user will give away a portion of his collateral to the LPers."},"getReserves((address,address,int8))":{"notice":"Returns the reserves of the vault meaning (1) the amount of collateral in the vault belonging to apes,(2) the amount of collateral belonging to LPers, and (3) the current collateral-debt-token price."},"initialize((address,address,int8))":{"notice":"Initialization is always necessary because we must deploy APE contracts, and possibly initialize the Oracle."},"mint(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256,uint144)":{"notice":"Function for minting APE or TEA, the protocol's synthetic tokens.When minting APE, the user will give away a portion of his deposited collateral to the LPers.When minting TEA, the user will give away a portion of his deposited collateral to protocol owned liquidity."},"totalReserves(address)":{"notice":"Global parameters for each type of collateral that aggregates amounts from all vaults (excluding fees to stakers) Fees to stakers can always be recovered by computing IERC20(collateral).balanceOf(address(this)) - params.isAPE: If true, burn APE. If false, burn TEA
params.vaultParams: The 3 parameters identifying a vault: collateral token, debt token, and leverage tier.

returns._0: amount of collateral obtained for burning APE or TEA.

mint(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256.details: The user can mint by depositing collateral token or debt token dependening on whether collateralToDepositMin is 0 or not, respectively.The user also has the option to mint with vanilla ETH when the token is WETH by simply sending ETH with the call. In this case, amountToDeposit is ignored.

params.amountToDeposit: Collateral amount to deposit if collateralToDepositMin == 0, debt token to deposit if collateralToDepositMin > 0
params.collateralToDepositMin: Ignored when minting with collateral token, otherwise it specifies the minimum amount of collateral to receive from Uniswap when swapping the debt token.
params.isAPE: If true, mint APE. If false, mint TEA
params.vaultParams: The 3 parameters identifying a vault: collateral token, debt token, and leverage tier.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.details: This callback function is required by Uniswap pools when making a swap.This function is exectuted when the user decides to mint TEA or APE with debt token.This function is in charge of sending the debt token to the uniswwap pool.It will revert if any external actor that is not a Uniswap pool calls this function.

updateSystemState(uint16,uint16,bool).details: All these parameters are update in a single function for minimize bytecode.All checks and balances to be done at system control

params.vaultParams: The 3 parameters identifying a vault: collateral token, debt token, and leverage tier.

returns.totalFeesToStakers: is the total amount of tokens to be distributed

params.to: is the recipient of the tokens
params.tokens: is a list of tokens to be withdrawn.

returns.amounts: is the list of amounts of tokens to be withdrawn

burn(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256.notice: Function for burning APE or TEA, the protocol's synthetic tokens.When burning APE, the user will give away a portion of his collateral to the LPers.

getReserves((address,address,int8)).notice: Returns the reserves of the vault meaning (1) the amount of collateral in the vault belonging to apes,(2) the amount of collateral belonging to LPers, and (3) the current collateral-debt-token price.

initialize((address,address,int8)).notice: Initialization is always necessary because we must deploy APE contracts, and possibly initialize the Oracle.

mint(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256.notice: Function for minting APE or TEA, the protocol's synthetic tokens.When minting APE, the user will give away a portion of his deposited collateral to the LPers.When minting TEA, the user will give away a portion of his deposited collateral to protocol owned liquidity.

totalReserves(address).notice: Global parameters for each type of collateral that aggregates amounts from all vaults (excluding fees to stakers) Fees to stakers can always be recovered by computing IERC20(collateral).balanceOf(address(this)) - totalReserves[collateral], so that if a token is accidentally sent to this contract, it becomes dividends for the stakers.

totalSupply(uint256).notice: The total circulating supply of TEA

updateSystemState(uint16,uint16,bool).notice: This function can only be called by the SystemControl contractIt updates the base fee charge to apes, the fee charged to LPers when minting or haults all minting.

updateVaults(uint48[],uint48[],uint8[],u.notice: Updates the tax of the vaults whose fees are distributed to stakers of SIR.The amount of SIR rewards received by LPers of a vault is proportional to the tax of the vault. 0 tax implies no SIR rewards.This function can only be called by the SystemControl contract.

vaultStates((address,address,int8)).notice: Returns the state of a particular vault

withdrawFees(address).notice: This function is only intended to be called by the SIR contract.The fees collected for SIR stakers are distributed to them.

withdrawToSaveSystem(address[],address).notice: This function is only intended to be called as last recourse to save the system from a critical bug or hackduring the beta period. To execute it, the system must be in Shutdown statuswhich can only be activated after SHUTDOWN_WITHDRAWAL_DELAY seconds elapsed since Emergency status was activated.
